issue.title: Cannot generate libsecp256k1.so in macOS Sierra (10.12.5)
issue.body:
We are trying to build bitcoin-s-core by following the instructions in https://github.com/Christewart/bitcoin-s-core/blob/master/BUILD_README.md. An error message occurred in config.log, conftest.c:11:10: fatal error: 'ac_nonexistent.h' file not found. The content of config.log is attached to the end of this report. Notice that running the make step describe in the BUILD_README.md does not generate the expected file, secp256k1/.libs/libsecp256k1.so.

The OS used is macOS Sierra (10.12.5). 

Per discussion with Chris, we have verified the following information:
$ autoconf --version
autoconf (GNU Autoconf) 2.69

$ openssl version
OpenSSL 1.0.2k 26 Jan 2017

$ brew --version
Homebrew 1.2.4
Homebrew/homebrew-core (git revision 19f04; last commit 2017-07-06)

$ brew install gmp
Warning: gmp 6.1.2 is already installed

events.body: I also get `fatal error: 'ac_nonexistent.h' file not found` error on Mojave. I tried for several ours to get it to work to no avail.

Copying from a comment by Alexy on the Bitcoin-s repository: https://github.com/bitcoin-s/bitcoin-s-core/issues/83#issuecomment-326999795

It's important to remember .so is called .dylib on Mac OS.

This all worked for me after
brew install automake
brew install libtool
...
cp -p libsecp256k1.0.dylib ../../lib/

I've also done, in lib/,

ln -s libsecp256k1.0.dylib libsecp256k1.dylib
ln -s libsecp256k1.0.dylib libsecp256k1.so

-- not sure if I need the symlinks, but just in case.

and call sbt with

sbt -Djava.library.path=lib

Feel free to reopen if there is an ongoing issue.
